==English==

===Etymology===
There are many theories as to where this idiom comes from, but a plausible one is as follows:
#A person standing on a [[pail]] or [[bucket]] with her head in a [[slip noose]] would kick the bucket so as to [[commit suicide]];

===Verb phrase===
'''[[kick]] the [[bucket]]'''

# {{idiom}} {{euphemism}} To [[die]]
#: ''The old horse finally '''kicked the bucket'''.''
# {{idiom}} {{slang}} Of a machine, to break down such that it cannot be repaired.
#: ''I think my sewing machine has '''kicked the bucket'''.''

